This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by White House Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton on Air Force One en route to Guadalajara, Mexico. Burton discusses the purpose of the summit in Mexico, which includes discussions on H1N1 preparedness, economic competitiveness, security, and global climate change. He also mentions that the President has been briefed on the Hudson River crash and that the President has had ongoing discussions with leaders in Canada and Mexico. Burton mentions that trucking and economic issues will be discussed, and he briefly mentions the progress being made in Afghanistan and Pakistan. He also mentions that the United States has expressed concern to Iran about the three hikers being detained.